-- Caterpillar plan to build diesel engines in China
-- 
-- Tue Aug 28, 2007 9:05am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/28/us-caterpillar-china-idUSWNAS297620070828

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Heavy equipment maker Caterpillar Inc. ( CAT.N ) said on Tuesday it plans to build small and medium-sized diesel engines in China. 

 Caterpillar said it has signed a non-binding memorandum of understanding with the Wuxi National High-Tech Industrial Development Zone outlining a significant multi-year investment to develop and manufacture Perkins and Caterpillar branded engines in Wuxi, which is in Jiangsu province. (Reporting by  Euan Rocha )